    <div id="what" class="dark-segment">
      <div class="regular-story">
        <h2><br>How it works</h2>      
        <h3>What's involved?</h3>
        <p>When I (Alex) wanted to start a meditation practice, it was a real struggle. I finally realized I needed to people to sit with, or it wouldn't happen. That's how I ended up at the Zendo, and it was a huge help. Our intent is to provide a community of support for you, as you start (or continue) your practice.</p>
        <ul>
        <li>weekly live video chat via hangouts</li>
        <li>online learning community</li>
        <li>one-on-one instruction opportunities</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Ok, here's the nitty gritty. Once you're signed up, you'll receive an email with information about the online community. Here, you'll learn about each week's topic, find links to resources like audio files and readings, and you'll be able to log your sitting practice and post questions or thoughts that come up. Once a week, we'll meet via Google Hangouts for a 90 minute session, including 20 minutes of meditation.</p>
        <p>This first time, we're offering the classes at half the price we expect to ask later &mdash; $180 instead of $360. (We'll also have scholarship slots in each class.)</p> 
        <p>The first session will be introductory instruction. In the next five weekly sessions, we'll typically start with a welcome and Q&amp;A, followed by a 20 minute session. Afterwards, a short talk on a topic related to mindfulness, and then we'll learn a supplemental technique for the following week's practice. Folks may enjoy staying after class for some social time.</p>
        <p>Between classes, we'll talk to one another in the online community. There you can post questions or discuss your experiences throughout the week. The instructors will be active in the community as well, answering questions and making fart jokes.</p>
        <p>Lastly, you'll also have the opportunity to sign up for a one-on-one sessions, in case there are questions you'd like to ask privately.</p>
      <p><a href="#signup">Take me to sign up</a><span class="arrow"><a href="#signup">&#10164;</a></span></p>
      </div>
