        <h2><br>Who's teaching?</h2>
        <h3>Instructor</h3>
        <p>Classes will be led by Alex Harms. Alex has been studying mindfulness techniques since 1985, and began teaching in 2007. She has studied formal logic, zen buddhism, humanistic psychology, with teachers including a Japanese trained zen priest<span class="note-indicator">*</span>, Marshall Rosenberg, Conal Elliott, Neale Donald Walsh, and Kim Krichbaum.</p>
        <p>Alex's practice is grounded in zen buddhism, with focus on cultivating curiosity, attention to body sensations, awareness of emotions, and a willingness to look at reality without flinching.</p>
<p class="note"><span class="note-indicator">*</span>...who shall remain nameless, because "lineage" isn't the point here. But if you want to know more, just ask. I'll introduce you! :)</p>
